## Quick Start (C)

```c
#include "telemetry_sdk.h"

telemetry_config_t cfg = {
    .endpoint_url = "{{ endpoint_url | default('https://telemetry.omnisight.local/api/v1/telemetry/ingest') }}",
    .device_id    = "{{ device_id | default('DEVICE_ID') }}",
    .profile      = "{{ sdk_profile | default('default') }}",
    .opt_in       = true,
};

telemetry_init(&cfg);

// Crash handler installed automatically after init
// Usage event:
telemetry_send_usage("feature_activated", "{ \"feature\": \"night_mode\" }");

// Performance metric:
telemetry_send_metric("cpu_percent", 42.5, "percent");
```

## Quick Start (Python)

```python
from telemetry_sdk import TelemetryClient

client = TelemetryClient(
    endpoint_url="{{ endpoint_url | default('https://telemetry.omnisight.local/api/v1/telemetry/ingest') }}",
    device_id="{{ device_id | default('DEVICE_ID') }}",
    profile="{{ sdk_profile | default('default') }}",
    opt_in=True,
)

# Crash handler installed automatically
# Usage event:
client.send_usage("feature_activated", metadata={"feature": "night_mode"})

# Performance metric:
client.send_metric("cpu_percent", 42.5, unit="percent")
```

## Privacy & Consent

Telemetry collection requires explicit opt-in from the device. The SDK
will queue events locally but will not transmit them until consent is
recorded.

### PII Fields Redacted

The following fields are automatically redacted before storage:

{% for field in pii_fields | default(["ip_address", "mac_address", "email"]) %}
- `{{ field }}`
{% endfor %}

## Dashboards

Three dashboards are available:

1. **Fleet Health** — active device count, heartbeat rate, error rate
2. **Crash Rate** — crash timeline, top signals, affected devices
3. **Feature Adoption** — daily active devices, feature usage, session duration

## Offline Queue Behavior

When network connectivity is lost:

1. Events are queued in persistent local storage (max {{ offline_queue_max_size | default(5000) }} events)
2. On reconnect, queued events are flushed in FIFO order
3. Flush respects batch size and rate limits
4. Events older than 24 hours are dropped from the queue

## Retention Policy

| Event Type | Retention | Archive After |
|---|---|---|
| crash_dump | 365 days | 90 days |
| usage_event | 90 days | 30 days |
| perf_metric | 30 days | 7 days |
